From 390a2ee9e21b27cda242bf290bb3e538abd74870 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Mon, 20 Apr 2026 10:37:06 +0200
Subject: [slayzone] slayzone: Phase 9.4 overlay routing
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Mojo-driven overlay swap for the Phase 9 overlay WebUIs. Shell region (or
any other region) can now call `layoutHost.showOverlay(id)` to cover the
BrowserView's content area with one of `{"leaderboard", "usage",
"context"}`; empty id closes the overlay and returns to whatever mode
was visible before.

layout.mojom:
- New `ShowOverlay(string overlay_id) => (bool ok)`. Empty id closes;
  unknown ids return ok=false with no state change (caller can render
  inline error).

SlayzoneOverlayManager (new):
- Owns a single lazy `views::WebView* overlay_webview_` parented as a
  child of SlayzoneBrowserView via the public `views::View::AddChildView`
  API. NO edits to `slayzone_browser_view.{h,cc}` — Phase 7 R3 terminal-
  slot work is still in flight in that file per orchestrator directive,
  and Phase 9.4 must ship without coordinating bounds-tracking into
  OnBoundsChanged. Instead the manager registers as a `views::ViewObserver`
  on the BrowserView and updates overlay bounds in OnViewBoundsChanged.
- `kOverlayIds` allowlist for `{"leaderboard", "usage", "context"}`.
- `ReorderChildView(overlay_webview_, -1)` on show to keep overlay on top
  of the region grid / home panel.
- `OnViewIsDeleting` clears refs so teardown order with LayoutHost doesn't
  UAF (manager is owned by LayoutHost which is owned by BrowserView).

SlayzoneLayoutHost:
- Owns `std::unique_ptr<SlayzoneOverlayManager> overlay_manager_`.
- New `ShowOverlay(overlay_id, callback)` forwards to the manager; returns
  false when no view is bound.

Scope fences held — ESC-to-close + `--slayzone-overlay=<id>` dev CLI
switch are deferred; both would touch SlayzoneBrowserView (accelerator
registration in focus chain + AddedToWidget parse). They land once the
Phase 7 R3 fence is lifted.
